17) locks
1. Padlock
A portable lock usually used on gates, lockers, chains, and storage units.
2. Deadbolt Lock
A strong door lock that uses a solid metal bolt to resist forced entry.
3. Mortise Lock
A lock installed inside a pocket cut into the door itself, often used in commercial doors.
4. Rim Lock
A lock mounted on the surface of a door rather than recessed inside it.
5. Night Latch
A common surface-mounted lock used on residential entrance doors.
6. Cam Lock
A simple lock commonly used on cabinets, drawers, mailboxes, and lockers.
7. Knob Lock
A lock built into a doorknob, usually used on interior doors or light duty doors.
8. Lever Handle Lock
A lock integrated into a lever handle, often used in schools, offices, and public buildings.
9. Cylinder Lock
A cylinder-based lock commonly used in modern uPVC and timber doors.
10. Multi-Point Lock
A door lock that secures at several points along the frame instead of just one point.


